citeinfo.title: PLSS Quarter-Sections Covering the Entire CMAP Region.

idinfo.native: Microsoft Windows XP Version 5.1 (Build 2600) Service Pack 3; ESRI ArcCatalog 9.3.0.1770

descript.abstract: This shapefile contains all quarter-sections in the CMAP service area, including those in Aux Sable Township in Grundy County. This file originated in 1995 at NIPC in coverage format for the counties of Cook, DuPage, Kane, Lake, McHenry and Will; and extended beyond those borders to include all PLSS quarter-sections that were represented on the USGS map sheets from which they were digitized. It was converted to shapefile format, reprojected to the NAD83 datum, and supplemented with Kendal County quarter-sections in 2005, using USGS DRGs of the 1:24,000 maps as a base instead of paper maps. The addition of the Aux Sable geometry was completed in October 2008 by David Clark using USGS DRGs. Subdivision of sections into quarter-sections for the Kendall and Grundy additions were done using methodology consistent with the original NIPC procedures.

dataIdInfo.idPurp: Modeling subzones used as CMAP's base geography for trip generation.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: These subzones are units of geography that are used in CMAP's transportation modeling activities. Subzone boundaries are derived from the Public Land Survey System (PLSS). This version of the CMAP modeling subzones differs from previous versions in that there are a few hundred more subzones. Previous Census-based subzone boundaries have been replaced to give all subzones PLSS-based boundaries.
